    <tag group="IsWeapon" tag="wLance"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wLance"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iSpectrDag" name="Spectral Dagger" description="Fashioned from a bone of a creature that died violently, this appears to be just a dagger hilt made of bone.  When a creature grasps the hilt, a dagger &quot;blade&quot; of light appears. (Treat the weapon as a dagger for proficiency, feats, and so on.)  The blade winks out when the hilt leaves the wielder&apos;s hand.\n\nThe spectral dagger has no attack bonus and deals no damage, but any target struck is affected by a {i}chill touch{/i} spell (DC 11).  Striking with the spectral dagger is considered a touch attack.  Creatures with multiple attacks may use the spectral dagger in a full attack action to strike more than once per round just as if they wielded a normal dagger.\nCaster Level: 5th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}chill touch{/i}; Market Price: 20,000 gp." compset="MagicWep" summary="Creatures must save (W 11) or be affected by {i}Chill Touch[/i}.">
    <comment>This uses DEX instead of STR for attack rolls.</comment>
    <fieldval field="wFixDamage" value="0"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="20000"/>
    <usesource source="UnApproach"/>
    <tag group="IsWeapon" tag="wDagger"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wDagger"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iThayanBom" name="Thayan Bombard" description="The Thayan bombard is a magical cannon that can launch a variety of dangerous or noxious bombs.  The effects depend on the missile launched.  Firing the weapon is a standard action, requiring a ranged touch attack to strike the desired space.  (The touch AC of an empty square is 5.)  The Thayan bombard has a range increment of 150 feet, and like any projectile weapon, can fire up to 10 range increments at the normal &#150;2 penalty per range increment.  If the ranged touch attack misses, resolve the bomb&#146;s effect as a grenadelike weapon (see Chapter 3: Running the Game in the {i}DUNGEON MASTER&#146;s Guide{/i}).\n\nOnce fired, the Thayan bombard requires three separate Profession (siege engineer) skill checks (DC 10) to clear, load with a new bomb, and prepare for firing.  A skilled crew of four can fire the weapon every round with a little cooperation, while a smaller or less proficient crew takes longer (although a single skilled character can fire the bombard once every 4 rounds, provided he makes successful checks).\n\nCaster Level: 9th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}telekinesis{/i}; Market Price: 22,500 gp; Weight: 500 lb.\n\nTypical bombs are listed below.  Most bombs are single-use magic items that can be triggered only through being launched from a Thayan bombard, although similar actions such as being flung from a catapult or hurled by a giant might also work.  A bomb is a thick glass sphere about 1 foot in diameter and weighing 20 pounds.\n\n{i}Cloudkill Bomb:{/i} This bomb is filled with a bilious green liquid.  When it hits, it creates a cloudkill spell triggered at and centered on the point of impact. The {i}cloudkill{/i} is stationary and does not move away from the point of impact.  Caster Level: 9th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}cloudkill{/i}; Market Price: 1,125 gp; Weight: 20 lb.\n\n{i}Death Bomb:{/i} Black and cold, this bomb is covered with sinister blue runes.  It creates a {i}circle of death{/i} triggered at and centered on its point of impact, slaying 11d4 Hit Dice of creatures.  Caster Level: 11th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}circle of death{/i}; Market Price: 1,650 gp; Weight: 20 lb.\n\n{i}Fireball Bomb:{/i} The most common magical bomb, this is warm to the touch and glows a dull, angry red.  It creates a fireball triggered at and centered on the point of impact.  These bombs come in three sizes: a 3d6, 6d6, or 10d6 {i}fireball{/i}.  Caster Level: 5th, 6th, or 10th, for 3d6, 6d6, or 10d6 {i}fireball{/i}, respectively; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}fireball{/i}; Market Price: 375 gp (3d6), 450 gp (6d6), or 750 gp (10d6); Weight: 20 lb.\n\n{i}Snowball Swarm Bomb:{/i} This bomb is blue and frost-covered.  It creates a {i}Snilloc&#146;s snowball swarm{/i} that deals 3d6 points of cold damage, triggered at and centered on the point of impact.  Caster Level: 5th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}Snilloc&#146;s snowball swarm{/i}; Market Price: 250 gp; Weight: 20 lb.\n\n{i}Stinking Cloud Bomb:{/i} Filled with a sickly yellow concoction, this bomb creates a stinking cloud triggered at and centered on the point of impact.  Caster Level: 5th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}stinking cloud{/i}; Market Price: 375 gp; Weight: 20 lb.\n\n{i}Stone Shot:{/i} Not a magical bomb at all but a simple stone shaped to fit the {i}Thayan bombard{/i}, a stone shot deals 3d6 points of damage.  The shot must be aimed at a creature, not a square, and it is resolved through a ranged attack (not a ranged touch attack).   Market Price: 5 gp; Weight: 30 lb." compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="22500"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="500"/>
    <usesource source="UnApproach"/>
    <tag group="EquipType" tag="Wood"/>
    <tag group="wRangeInc" tag="150"/>
    <tag group="wCategory" tag="RangeProj"/>
    <tag group="EquipType" tag="Metal"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iYuirGhstB" name="Yuir Ghostblade" description="Made by the star elves to battle the extradimensional marauders threatening their home, this {b}+1 aberration bane ghost touch longsword{/b} also confers a +2 deflection bonus to the wielder&#146;s Armor Class.\nCaster Level: 9th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}dimensional anchor{/i}, {i}plane shift{/i}, {i}shield of faith{/i}, {i}summon monster I{/i}; Market Price: 44,315 gp; Cost to Create: 22,315 gp + 1,760 XP." compset="MagicWep" summary="+1 Aberration Bane Ghost Touch Longsword, +2 Deflection Bon.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="44315"/>
    <fieldval field="gSizeCost" value="2500"/>
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="2"/>
    <usesource source="UnApproach"/>
    <eval phase="First"><![CDATA[ if (field[gIsEquip].value + field[wIs2nd].value <> 0) then
     ~ Add a +2 Morale Bonus to our armor class
     hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACDeflect].value = maximum(hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACDeflect].value, 2)
 endif]]></eval>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wLongsword"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioBreaSton" name="Breachstone" description="Breachstone: A smooth stone token carved with runes on both sides, the breachstone need only be touched to a wall or barrier to create a passwall as cast by a 10th-level sorcerer.  The breachstone&#146;s tunnel is 5 feet wide, 8 feet tall, and up to 10 feet long. The tunnel remains in existence as long as the breachstone remains in the passage, and it closes 1 round after the breachstone is removed.  As with passwall, the breachstone can only create an opening in stone, wood, or plaster walls, not through metal or magical walls.  (A wall of stone is not magical after it has been created.)  The breachstone operates five times and then crumbles into dust.\n\nCaster Level: 9th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}passwall{/i}; Market Price: 10,000 gp; Weight: &#151;." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="1000"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="5"/>
    <fieldval field="hName1" value="Uses"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCirWilde" name="Circlet of the Wilderness" description="When placed on the head of a ranger, this band of braided strands of wood grants the wearer a number of spell-like abilities.  Each function requires a different command word.  At will&#151;{i}calm animals{/i} (DC 11), {i}pass without trace{/i}, {i}speak with animals{/i}; 3/day&#151;{i}summon nature&#146;s ally I{/i}, {i}cure light wounds{/i} (DC 11); 1/day&#151;{i}summon nature&#146;s ally II{/i}, {i}cure serious wounds{/i} (DC 16).  These abilities are as the spells cast by a 7th-level druid.\n\nThe wearer of the circlet of the wilderness can also predict all naturally occurring weather within fifty miles of his current location for the next 24 hours, at will.  He cannot predict the use of weather-altering magic by someone else.\n\nThe Simbul sometimes awards these wondrous items to Aglarondan rangers who have proven their loyalty to her and their country through some great act of heroism.\n\nCaster Level: 7th; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}animal friendship{/i}, {i}cure light wounds{/i}, {i}cure serious wounds{/i}, {i}pass without trace{/i}, {i}speak with animals{/i}, {i}summon nature&#146;s ally I{/i}, {i}summon nature&#146;s ally II{/i}; Market Price: 50,000 gp. Weight &#151;." compset="Wondrous">
    <comment>Need to Boostrap charges</comment>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="50000"/>
    <usesource source="UnApproach"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpHead"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioHthMDisg" name="Hathran Mask of Disguise" description="In its normal form, this mask is usually decorated with carved wavy lines and small, plain bird feathers.  It functions as a hat of disguise, although it changes only the wearer&#146;s face (the mask also adjusts to accommodate the disguise, appearing as a circlet, comb, hat, or similar item worn on the face or head).\n\nCaster Level: 2nd; Prerequisites: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}change self{/i}; Market Price: 1,000 gp; Weight: &#151;." compset="Wondrous">
