    <eval phase="Render" index="2"><![CDATA[    var CL as number
    CL = herofield[tHitDice].value

     field[xSumm].text = "" & field[hTotal].value & "/day use {i}Shadow Spray{/i} (CL" & CL & ") (DC F" & field[Value].value & ")"]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[    var charges as number
    var CL as number
    CL = herofield[tHitDice].value

    if (CL >= 9) then
       charges = 3
    else
       charges = 0
       field[xSumm].text = "You have no daily uses of this ability."
    endif

     
      if (charges = 0) then
        perform delete[Helper.ShowSpec]
        perform delete[Helper.ShowCharge]
      endif

    field[hTotal].value = charges

~ Count our Racial HD and get our base DC.
      var DC as number
      DC = 10 + CL/2 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value 
      DC = round(DC, 0, -1)

      field[Value].value = DC]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xShdwWalk" name="Shadow Walk" description="Illusion (Shadow)\nRange: Touch\nTarget: Up to one touched creature/level\nDuration: 1 hour/level (D)\nSaving Throw: Will negates\nSpell Resistance: Yes\n\nTo use the shadow walk spell, you must be in an area of shadowy illumination. You and any creature you touch are then transported along a coiling path of shadowstuff to the edge of the Material Plane where it borders the Plane of Shadow. The effect is largely illusory, but the path is quasi-real. You can take more than one creature along with you (subject to your level limit), but all must be touching each other.\n\nIn the region of shadow, you move at a rate of 50 miles per hour, moving normally on the borders of the Plane of Shadow but much more rapidly relative to the Material Plane. Thus, you can use this spell to travel rapidly by stepping onto the Plane of Shadow, moving the desired distance, and then stepping back onto the Material Plane.\n\nBecause of the blurring of reality between the Plane of Shadow and the Material Plane, you can&apos;t make out details of the terrain or areas you pass over during transit, nor can you predict perfectly where your travel will end. It&apos;s impossible to judge distances accurately, making the spell virtually useless for scouting or spying. Furthermore, when the spell effect ends, you are shunted 1d10&#215;100 feet in a random horizontal direction from your desired endpoint. If this would place you within a solid object, you are shunted 1d10&#215;1,000 feet in the same direction. If this would still place you within a solid object, you (and any creatures with you) are shunted to the nearest empty space available, but the strain of this activity renders each creature fatigued (no save).\n\nShadow walk can also be used to travel to other planes that border on the Plane of Shadow, but this usage requires the transit of the Plane of Shadow to arrive at a border with another plane of reality. The transit of the Plane of Shadow requires 1d4 hours.\n\nAny creatures touched by you when shadow walk is cast also make the transition to the borders of the Plane of Shadow. They may opt to follow you, wander off through the plane, or stumble back into the Material Plane (50% chance for either of the latter results if they are lost or abandoned by you). Creatures unwilling to accompany you into the Plane of Shadow receive a Will saving throw, negating the effect if successful." compset="Special">
    <usesource source="UnApproach"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge" name="Initial Damage" abbrev="Initial Damage"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="SpellLike"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="PickFocus"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="Render" index="2"><![CDATA[  var charges as number
  var CL as number
  CL = herofield[tHitDice].value

  if (CL >= 19) then
     charges = 3
  elseif (CL >= 11) then
     charges = 1
  endif

~Check if we have Telflammar Shadowlord levels, increase charges and remove extra specials
  if (#levelcount[TelflShdw] >= 3) then
   charges += 1
  foreach pick in hero from BaseSpec where "thingid.xShdwWalk & !SpecSource.cHelpThf"
   perform eachpick.delete[Helper.ShowSpec]
   perform eachpick.delete[Helper.ShowCharge]
  nexteach
  endif

  field[hTotal].value = charges

~ Count our Racial HD and get our base DC.
  var DC as number
  DC = 10 + CL/2 + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
  DC = round(DC, 0, -1)

  field[xSumm].text = "" & field[hTotal].value & "/day use {i}Shadow Walk{/i} (CL" & CL & ") (DC W" & DC & ")"]]></eval>
    </thing>
