  <thing id="sThfShMsk" name="Shadow Mask" description="{i}You draw raw energy from the Plane of Shadow to obscure your face. {/i}\n\nYou cause a mask of shadows to form around your face. It does not impede your vision, cannot be physically removed, completely hides your features, and protects you against certain attacks. You receive a +4 bonus on saving throws against light or darkness spells and any spells that rely on bright light for damaging effects, such as the {i}flare{/i} spell or the fireworks effect of {i}pyrotechnics{/i}. You also gain a 50% chance each round to avoid having to make a saving throw against gaze attacks, just as if you averted your eyes. If you avert your eyes while using {i}shadow mask{/i}, you get to check twice to see if you avoid having to make the saving throw.\n\nWhen the spell&#146;s duration ends, the {i}shadow mask{/i} fades over the course of 1d4 rounds (rather than immediately), giving you time to keep your face hidden by other means. A successful {i}dispel magic{/i} cast against a {i}shadow mask{/i} effectively ends the spell and causes the same slow fading.\n\n{i}Material Component{/i}: A mask of black cloth." compset="Spell" summary="Grants +4 on saves against light spells, protection from gaze attacks.">
